<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Execution" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Execution,</orth> 1) a carrying into effect, performance: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 3, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.260" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 260</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.99" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.346" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 346</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 105</bibl>.<lb />2) action, working: <cit><quote>scarce I can refrain the e. of my big-swoln heart upon that Clifford,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 111</bibl></cit>. <emph>by reason guide his</emph> (the ram's) <cit><quote>e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.210" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 210</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the sway, revenue, e. of the rest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the e. of his wit, hands, heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.466" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 466</bibl></cit>.

<lb />3) any deed of hostility and violence, blows, slaughter, destruction: <cit><quote>be swift like lightning in the e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>holds his infant up and hangs resolved correction in the arm that was upreared to e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.214" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 214</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>retreat is made and e. stayed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>doing the e. and the act for which we have assembled them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hath done to-day mad and fantastic e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to do some fatal e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 36</bibl></cit>. <emph>his brandished steel, which smoked with bloody e.</emph> Mcb. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl> With <emph>on</emph>: <cit><quote>do e. on the watch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 35</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.76" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 76</bibl>. <cit><quote>thy cruelty in e. upon offenders hath exceeded law,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.135" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 135</bibl></cit>.
<lb />4) death lawfully inflicted: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 2, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 5.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 121</bibl>. Wint. <bibl n="shak. err 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. err 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 1, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.99" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.46" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.121" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.4.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 72</bibl>. <cit><quote>is e. done on Cawdor?</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 4, 1</bibl></cit>.
